Extend your left arm over your head, creating a line from fingertips to back heel
Feel the stretch along the left side of your body
Keep your front knee tracking over your ankle
Breathe deeply while holding the pose
Switch sides and repeat with left leg forward

products.title: Extended side Angle Pose With Block
products.description: This modified version of extended side angle pose uses a yoga block for support, making the pose more accessible for beginners or those with limited flexibility. The block helps maintain proper alignment while still providing the benefits of the traditional pose.
steps: Set up in warrior II position with a yoga block nearby
Place the block on the floor inside your front leg
Adjust the block height to high, medium, or low as needed
Rest your bottom hand on the block instead of your thigh
Extend your top arm over your head
Maintain the side body stretch while using the block for support
Keep your front knee aligned over your ankle
Hold the pose and repeat on the other side

products.title: Elevated Pike Shoulder Shrug
products.description: The elevated pike shoulder shrug is a bodyweight exercise that targets the trapezius and shoulder stabilizers from an inverted position. This exercise helps build shoulder strength and stability while preparing the body for more advanced movements like handstands.
steps: Start in a downward dog position with feet elevated on a box or bench
Walk your hands closer to the elevation to create a pike position
Keep your arms straight and core engaged
Lower your shoulders by allowing your shoulder blades to spread apart
Push through your hands to elevate your shoulders and squeeze your shoulder blades together
Focus on the movement coming from your shoulders, not your arms
Repeat the shrugging motion for the desired number of repetitions
Maintain the pike position throughout the entire movement

products.title: Easy Seated Twist Pose
products.description: Easy seated twist pose is a gentle spinal rotation that helps improve spinal mobility and releases tension in the back and hips. This accessible pose can be performed by people of all flexibility levels and is excellent for counteracting the effects of prolonged sitting.
steps: Sit cross-legged on the floor or in a comfortable seated position
Place your right hand behind you for support
Rest your left hand on your right knee
Lengthen your spine by sitting tall
Gently twist your torso to the right, starting from your lower back
Keep your hips facing forward while your torso rotates
Hold the twist while breathing deeply
Return to center and repeat the twist to the left side

products.title: Easy Pose Neck Stretch
products.description: Easy pose neck stretch combines the grounded stability of a seated meditation posture with gentle neck stretches. This combination helps relieve neck tension while promoting relaxation and mindfulness, making it perfect for stress relief and posture improvement.
steps: Sit in a comfortable cross-legged position
Rest your hands gently on your knees
Lengthen your spine and relax your shoulders
Slowly drop your right ear toward your right shoulder
Feel the gentle stretch along the left side of your neck
Hold for 15-30 seconds while breathing deeply
Return your head to center
Repeat the stretch on the left side

products.title: Eagle Arms Chin Into Chest
products.description: Eagle arms chin into chest combines the shoulder stretch of eagle arms with a forward head position to create a comprehensive upper body stretch. This pose targets the upper back, shoulders, and neck while helping to counteract forward head posture from desk work.
steps: Wrap your arms around yourself in eagle arms position
Bring your right arm under your left, wrapping around
Try to press your palms together if possible
Lift your elbows while keeping shoulders away from ears
Gently tuck your chin toward your chest
Feel the stretch across your upper back and between your shoulder blades
Hold the position while breathing deeply
Release and repeat with the opposite arm on top

products.title: Dumbbell Swing
products.description: The dumbbell swing is a dynamic hip-hinge movement that targets the posterior chain muscles including the glutes, hamstrings, and core. This explosive exercise builds power, improves cardiovascular fitness, and develops functional strength for everyday movements.
steps: Hold a dumbbell with both hands, arms extended
Stand with feet slightly wider than shoulder-width apart
Hinge at the hips and lower the dumbbell between your legs
Keep your back straight and chest up
Explosively drive your hips forward to swing the dumbbell up
Let the momentum carry the dumbbell to chest height
Control the descent by hinging at the hips again
Maintain a fluid, rhythmic swinging motion

products.title: Dumbbell Suitcase Crunch
products.description: The dumbbell suitcase crunch is a core exercise that simulates the motion of closing a suitcase while holding weight. This movement targets the rectus abdominis and hip flexors while adding resistance to increase the challenge and build stronger abdominal muscles.
steps: Lie on your back holding a dumbbell with both hands
Extend your arms overhead and legs straight out
Simultaneously bring your knees toward your chest
Crunch your upper body up, bringing the dumbbell toward your knees
Squeeze your abs at the top of the movement
Slowly return to the starting position with control
Keep your lower back pressed into the floor
Focus on using your core muscles to initiate the movement

products.title: Dumbbell Standing Hip Abduction
products.description: Dumbbell standing hip abduction is a unilateral exercise that targets the gluteus medius and other hip abductor muscles. This exercise helps improve hip stability, correct muscle imbalances, and strengthen the muscles responsible for lateral leg movement and pelvic stability.
steps: Stand upright holding a dumbbell in one hand
Hold onto a stable surface with your free hand for balance
Attach the dumbbell to your ankle or hold it against your outer thigh
Keep your standing leg straight and core engaged
Lift your weighted leg out to the side as high as comfortable
Focus on using your hip muscles, not momentum
Lower your leg back to the starting position with control
Complete all repetitions before switching to the other leg

products.title: Dumbbell Staggered Hip thrust
products.description: The dumbbell staggered hip thrust is an advanced variation that involves placing one foot forward and one back to create an asymmetrical stance. This unilateral emphasis challenges stability while maximally targeting the glutes and improving hip strength imbalances.
steps: Sit with your upper back against a bench, placing a dumbbell on your hips
Position one foot closer to the bench and one foot further away in a staggered stance
Keep your core engaged and maintain the staggered foot position
Drive through your heels to lift your hips toward the ceiling
Focus on the working leg while maintaining balance
Squeeze your glutes hard at the top of the movement
Lower with control while maintaining the staggered position
Complete all reps before switching the staggered leg position

products.title: Dumbbell Staggered Glute Bridge
products.description: The dumbbell staggered glute bridge uses an asymmetrical foot position to create unilateral emphasis while maintaining ground contact with both feet. This variation increases the challenge on one glute while improving stability and addressing muscle imbalances.
steps: Lie on your back with a dumbbell positioned on your hips
Place one foot closer to your glutes and one foot further away
Keep both feet flat on the ground in the staggered position
Drive through your heels to lift your hips off the ground
Focus on the glute of the leg positioned closer to your body
Squeeze your glutes at the top and create a straight line
Lower your hips back down with control
Complete all reps before switching the staggered leg position

products.title: Dumbbell Staggered Deadlift
products.description: The dumbbell staggered deadlift uses an asymmetrical foot position with one foot slightly forward to increase the challenge on the posterior chain while improving balance and stability. This variation helps identify and correct strength imbalances between legs.
steps: Stand with one foot slightly forward in a staggered stance
Hold a dumbbell in each hand with arms extended
Keep most of your weight on your front leg
Hinge at the hips by pushing them back and lowering the dumbbells
Maintain a neutral spine and keep your chest up
Feel the stretch in your hamstrings of the front leg
Drive through your front heel to return to standing
Complete all reps before switching the staggered leg position

products.title: Dumbbell Skullcrusher
products.description: The dumbbell skullcrusher is an isolation exercise that targets the triceps brachii by extending the elbows from a flexed position. This exercise effectively builds tricep strength and size while allowing for unilateral training to address muscle imbalances.
steps: Lie on a bench holding a dumbbell in each hand
Extend your arms straight up above your chest
Keep your upper arms stationary throughout the movement
Lower the dumbbells by bending only at the elbows
Bring the weights toward your forehead in a controlled motion
Feel the stretch in your triceps at the bottom position
Extend your elbows to press the dumbbells back to starting position
Keep your core engaged and avoid arching your back

products.title: Dumbbell Single Leg Single Arm Deadlift
products.description: The dumbbell single leg single arm deadlift is an advanced unilateral exercise that challenges balance, coordination, and posterior chain strength. This movement targets the hamstrings, glutes, and back while significantly challenging core stability and proprioception.
steps: Stand on one leg holding a dumbbell in the opposite hand
Keep your standing leg slightly bent and core engaged
Hinge at the hip by pushing your free leg back behind you
Lower the dumbbell toward the ground while maintaining balance
Keep your back straight and chest up throughout the movement
Feel the stretch in the hamstring of your standing leg
Drive through your standing heel to return to upright position
Complete all reps before switching sides

products.title: Dumbbell Single Leg Hip Thrust
products.description: The dumbbell single leg hip thrust is a unilateral exercise that maximally targets one glute at a time while challenging stability and balance. This advanced variation helps identify and correct strength imbalances while building powerful hip extension strength.
steps: Sit with your upper back against a bench, dumbbell on your hips
Plant one foot firmly on the ground, extend the other leg straight out
Keep your working leg's foot flat and positioned under your knee
Drive through your planted heel to lift your hips up
Focus on maximally contracting the glute of your working leg
Keep your extended leg straight and in line with your body
Hold the top position briefly for maximum activation
Lower with control and complete all reps before switching legs

products.title: Dumbbell Single Arm Upright Row
products.description: The dumbbell single arm upright row targets the deltoids, trapezius, and rhomboids while allowing for unilateral training to address muscle imbalances. This exercise builds shoulder strength and upper back development while improving posture.
steps: Stand with feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand
Let the dumbbell hang in front of your thigh with arm extended
Keep your core engaged and maintain good posture
Pull the dumbbell straight up along your body, leading with your elbow
Lift until your elbow is slightly above shoulder height
Keep the dumbbell close to your body throughout the movement
Lower the weight back to the starting position with control
Complete all repetitions before switching to the other arm

products.title: Dumbbell Silverback Shrug
products.description: The dumbbell silverback shrug is a variation that emphasizes the backward and upward movement of the shoulders to target the upper trapezius. This exercise helps build thick, powerful traps while improving posture and upper back strength.
steps: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding dumbbells at your sides
Keep your arms straight and core engaged
Pull your shoulders back and up in a circular motion
Emphasize the backward component to target the traps effectively
Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top
Hold the contraction briefly
Lower your shoulders back to the starting position slowly
Avoid rolling your shoulders forward during the movement

products.title: Dumbbell Side Plank Up Down
products.description: The dumbbell side plank up down is a dynamic core exercise that combines lateral stability with additional resistance. This movement targets the obliques, transverse abdominis, and shoulder stabilizers while challenging coordination and balance.
steps: Start in a side plank position holding a dumbbell in your top hand
Keep your body in a straight line from head to feet
Lower from your hand to your forearm while maintaining the side plank
Press back up to the hand position
Keep your hips elevated and core engaged throughout
Control the dumbbell to prevent it from pulling you off balance
Maintain proper alignment without rotating your torso
Complete all reps before switching to the other side

products.title: Dumbbell Shoulder Extension
products.description: The dumbbell shoulder extension targets the posterior deltoids and latissimus dorsi by moving the arms behind the body. This exercise helps improve shoulder mobility, strengthen the rear delts, and balance shoulder development by working the often-neglected posterior muscles.
steps: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding dumbbells in both hands
Start with arms extended forward at chest level
Keep your core engaged and maintain upright posture
Pull the dumbbells back behind your body by extending your shoulders
Focus on squeezing your shoulder blades together
Feel the contraction in your rear delts and lats
Return to the starting position with control
Maintain tension throughout the entire range of motion

products.title: Dumbbell Seated Zottman Curl
products.description: The dumbbell seated Zottman curl combines a traditional bicep curl with a reverse curl by rotating the wrists during the movement. This exercise targets both the biceps and forearms while being performed in a seated position for better isolation and stability.
steps: Sit on a bench with dumbbells in each hand, palms facing forward
Keep your elbows close to your sides throughout the movement
Curl the weights up using a traditional bicep curl motion
At the top, rotate your wrists so palms face downward
Lower the weights slowly in this reverse grip position
At the bottom, rotate your wrists back to the starting position
Focus on controlling both the concentric and eccentric phases
Maintain seated posture without using momentum

products.title: Dumbbell Plank Pullthrough
products.description: The dumbbell plank pullthrough is a dynamic core exercise that combines plank stability with anti-rotation strength. This movement challenges the core to resist rotation while pulling a dumbbell from one side to the other underneath the body.
steps: Start in a plank position with a dumbbell placed to one side
Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels
Reach under your body with the opposite hand to grab the dumbbell
Pull the dumbbell across to the other side while maintaining plank position
Resist the urge to rotate your hips or shoulders
Place the dumbbell on the opposite side
Return to plank position and repeat pulling from the other direction
Keep your core engaged throughout the entire movement

products.title: Dumbbell Pendlay Row
products.description: The dumbbell Pendlay row is performed from a bent-over position with the dumbbells starting from the floor each rep. This variation emphasizes explosive pulling power and targets the latissimus dorsi, rhomboids, and middle trapezius while building back strength and power.
steps: Place dumbbells on the floor and stand with feet hip-width apart
Hinge at the hips to bend over with a straight back
Grip the dumbbells with your torso parallel to the floor
Explosively pull the dumbbells to your lower ribcage
Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top
Lower the dumbbells back to the floor completely
Reset your position before performing the next repetition
Maintain a flat back throughout the entire movement

products.title: Dumbbell Overhead Side Bend
products.description: The dumbbell overhead side bend targets the obliques and lateral core muscles while holding a weight overhead. This exercise challenges both core stability and shoulder stability while building lateral flexion strength and improving spinal mobility.
steps: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell overhead
Keep the dumbbell directly above your head with arm extended
Engage your core and maintain an upright posture
Slowly bend to one side, feeling the stretch in your obliques
Keep your arm holding the dumbbell straight overhead
Return to the center position with control
Bend to the opposite side to complete one full repetition
Maintain shoulder stability throughout the movement

products.title: Dumbbell Offset Squat
products.description: The dumbbell offset squat involves holding weight on only one side of the body to create an unbalanced load. This challenges the core to work harder to maintain proper alignment while building leg strength and improving unilateral stability.
steps: Hold a dumbbell in one hand at shoulder height
Stand with feet shoulder-width apart
Keep your chest up and core engaged to counteract the offset load
Initiate the squat by pushing your hips back and bending your knees
Descend until your thighs are parallel to the floor
Fight against the tendency to lean toward the weighted side
Drive through your heels to return to the standing position
Complete all reps before switching the dumbbell to the other side

products.title: Dumbbell Laying Silverback Shrug
products.description: The dumbbell laying silverback shrug is performed lying down to target the trapezius muscles from a different angle. This position eliminates momentum and provides constant tension on the traps while reducing stress on the spine.
steps: Lie face down on an incline bench holding dumbbells
Let your arms hang straight down with dumbbells in each hand
Keep your chest supported by the bench
Pull your shoulders back and up in a circular motion
Emphasize the backward movement to target the traps
Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top
Hold the contraction briefly
Lower your shoulders back to the starting position slowly

products.title: Dumbbell Laying 30 Degree Shrug
products.description: The dumbbell laying 30 degree shrug is performed on an inclined bench set to 30 degrees to target the trapezius muscles from a specific angle. This position provides excellent muscle isolation while reducing the involvement of other muscle groups.
steps: Set an incline bench to 30 degrees and lie face down
Hold dumbbells in each hand, letting them hang straight down
Keep your chest pressed against the bench for support
Raise your shoulders up toward your ears
Focus on contracting your trapezius muscles
Squeeze at the top of the movement
Lower your shoulders back down slowly
Maintain control throughout the entire range of motion

products.title: Dumbbell Kneeling Wood Chopper
products.description: The dumbbell kneeling wood chopper is a rotational core exercise performed from a kneeling position. This movement targets the obliques, transverse abdominis, and shoulders while improving rotational power and core stability from a stable base.
steps: Kneel on both knees holding a dumbbell with both hands
Start with the dumbbell at one side of your body above shoulder height
Rotate your torso and chop the dumbbell down across your body
Bring the weight to the opposite side near your hip
Keep your core engaged throughout the rotational movement
Return to the starting position with control
Complete all reps on one side before switching directions
Focus on rotating from your core, not just your arms

products.title: Dumbbell Knee Lawnmower Row
products.description: The dumbbell knee lawnmower row mimics the motion of starting a lawnmower while providing an explosive rowing movement. This exercise targets the latissimus dorsi, rhomboids, and middle trapezius while developing pulling power and coordination.
steps: Stand with feet staggered, holding a dumbbell in one hand
Bend at the hips and knees, similar to a lawnmower starting position
Let the dumbbell hang down toward the ground
Explosively pull the dumbbell up and back like starting a lawnmower
Drive your elbow back and squeeze your shoulder blade
Focus on the quick, powerful pulling motion
Lower the weight back to the starting position
Complete all reps before switching to the other arm

products.title: Dumbbell Hex Press
products.description: The dumbbell hex press is a chest exercise where the dumbbells are pressed together throughout the movement. This creates constant tension in the chest muscles while also engaging the triceps and anterior deltoids, making it an effective isolation exercise for chest development.
steps: Lie on a bench holding hexagonal dumbbells against each other
Press the flat sides of the dumbbells together at chest level
Keep the dumbbells pressed together throughout the entire movement
Press the weights straight up while maintaining contact between them
Squeeze your chest muscles as you press up
Lower the weights back to chest level slowly
Maintain constant pressure between the dumbbells
Focus on feeling the contraction in your chest muscles

products.title: Dumbbell Hand Side Plank
products.description: The dumbbell hand side plank is a lateral core strengthening exercise performed on the hand while holding additional weight. This exercise targets the obliques, transverse abdominis, and shoulder stabilizers while challenging balance and coordination.
steps: Start in a side plank position supported on one hand
Hold a dumbbell in your top hand
Keep your body in a straight line from head to feet
Engage your core to maintain the side plank position
Hold the position while controlling the dumbbell
Avoid letting your hips sag or rotate
Breathe steadily while maintaining the position
Complete the hold time before switching to the other side

products.title: Dumbbell Half Kneeling Wood Chopper
products.description: The dumbbell half kneeling wood chopper is a rotational core exercise performed from a half kneeling position. This asymmetrical stance challenges stability while building rotational power and targeting the obliques, transverse abdominis, and shoulders.
steps: Get into a half kneeling position with one knee up, one knee down
Hold a dumbbell with both hands at one side of your body
Start with the weight above the shoulder on the side of your up leg
Rotate your torso and chop the dumbbell down across your body
Bring the weight toward the hip of your down leg
Keep your core engaged throughout the rotation
Return to the starting position with control
Complete all reps before switching knee positions and chopping direction

products.title: Dumbbell Goblet Reverse Lunge
products.description: The dumbbell goblet reverse lunge combines the benefits of the reverse lunge with the goblet hold position. Holding the weight at chest level challenges the core and upper body while the reverse stepping motion targets the quadriceps, glutes, and hamstrings.
steps: Hold a dumbbell vertically at chest level with both hands
Stand tall with feet hip-width apart
Keep the dumbbell close to your chest throughout the movement
Step one foot back approximately 2-3 feet
Lower your body until both knees are bent to 90 degrees
Keep your front knee aligned over your ankle
Push through your front heel to return to starting position
Complete all reps on one leg before switching sides

products.title: Dumbbell Goblet Good Morning
products.description: The dumbbell goblet good morning is a hip hinge movement that targets the hamstrings, glutes, and erector spinae. Holding the weight at chest level creates a counterbalance that helps maintain proper form while building posterior chain strength.
steps: Hold a dumbbell vertically at chest level with both hands
Stand with feet hip-width apart, knees slightly bent
Keep the dumbbell close to your chest throughout the movement
Hinge at the hips by pushing them back
Lower your torso while keeping your back straight
Feel the stretch in your hamstrings
Drive your hips forward to return to the upright position
Keep your core engaged throughout the movement

products.title: Dumbbell Goblet Forward Lunge
products.description: The dumbbell goblet forward lunge combines the forward stepping lunge with a goblet hold position. This exercise targets the quadriceps, glutes, and hamstrings while the goblet position engages the core and upper body for additional stability.
steps: Hold a dumbbell vertically at chest level with both hands
Stand tall with feet hip-width apart
Keep the dumbbell close to your chest throughout
Step forward with one leg into a lunge position
Lower until both knees are bent to approximately 90 degrees
Keep your front knee aligned over your ankle
Push off your front foot to return to starting position
Alternate legs or complete all reps on one side first

products.title: Dumbbell Frog Jumps
products.description: Dumbbell frog jumps add resistance to the traditional frog jump movement, creating a more challenging plyometric exercise. This movement builds explosive lower body power while improving cardiovascular endurance and coordination.
steps: Hold a dumbbell with both hands at chest level
Start in a deep squat position with feet wider than shoulder-width
Keep the dumbbell close to your body throughout
Explosively jump forward while maintaining the squat position
Land softly back in the deep squat
Immediately prepare for the next jump without standing up
Continue jumping forward in the frog-like motion
Focus on controlled landings to protect your joints

products.title: Dumbbell Figure Four Hip Thrust
products.description: The dumbbell figure four hip thrust combines hip thrust mechanics with a figure four leg position. This creates deeper glute activation while also targeting the piriformis and other deep hip muscles for improved hip mobility and strength.
steps: Sit with your upper back against a bench, dumbbell on your hips
Place one ankle on top of the opposite knee in figure four position
Keep your planted foot flat on the ground
Drive through your planted heel to lift your hips up
Focus on contracting the glute of your planted leg
Feel the stretch in the hip of your figure four leg
Hold the top position briefly
Lower with control and complete all reps before switching sides

products.title: Dumbbell Figure Four Glute Bridge
products.description: The dumbbell figure four glute bridge targets the glutes while incorporating a hip mobility component. The figure four leg position creates a deeper stretch and more targeted activation of the working glute while challenging balance and stability.
steps: Lie on your back with a dumbbell positioned on your hips
Place one ankle on top of the opposite knee in figure four position
Keep your planted foot flat on the floor
Drive through your planted heel to lift your hips up
Focus on squeezing the glute of your planted leg
Feel the stretch in the hip of your figure four leg
Create a straight line from your knee to shoulder
Lower with control and complete all reps before switching sides

products.title: Dumbbell Feet Elevated Staggered Glute Bridge
products.description: The dumbbell feet elevated staggered glute bridge combines elevation with a staggered foot position to increase range of motion and unilateral emphasis. This advanced variation maximally challenges the glutes while improving hip stability and addressing imbalances.
steps: Lie on your back with feet elevated on a bench or platform
Place a dumbbell on your hips and position feet in staggered stance
Keep both feet on the elevated surface but staggered front to back
Drive through your heels to lift your hips higher than normal
Focus on the glute of the leg positioned closer to your body
Squeeze your glutes at the top with increased range of motion
Lower your hips below the starting level for full range
Complete all reps before switching the staggered position

products.title: Dumbbell Feet Elevated Single Leg Glute Bridge
products.description: The dumbbell feet elevated single leg glute bridge is an advanced unilateral exercise that combines elevation with single leg training. This maximally challenges one glute at a time while requiring significant balance, stability, and strength.
steps: Lie on your back with one foot elevated on a bench or platform
Place a dumbbell on your hips and extend the other leg straight out
Keep your working foot planted firmly on the elevated surface
Drive through your planted heel to lift your hips up high
Focus on maximally contracting the glute of your working leg
Keep your extended leg straight and in line with your body
Achieve greater range of motion due to the elevation
Lower with control and complete all reps before switching legs

products.title: Dumbbell Feet Elevated Glute Bridge
products.description: The dumbbell feet elevated glute bridge is an advanced variation that targets the gluteus maximus, gluteus medius, and hamstrings. Elevating the feet increases the range of motion and intensifies glute activation, making it more challenging than the standard bridge while building powerful hip extension and glute strength.
steps: Lie on your back with your feet elevated on a bench or platform
Position your feet hip-width apart on the elevated surface
Place a dumbbell across your hips, holding it securely
Keep your arms at your sides for stability and support the weight
Drive through your heels to lift your hips up toward the ceiling
Squeeze your glutes hard at the top, creating a straight line from knees to shoulders
Feel the increased stretch in your glutes due to the elevation
Lower your hips slowly back toward the ground with control
Stop just before your glutes touch the floor to maintain tension

products.title: Dumbbell Feet Elevated Figure Four Glute Bridge
products.description: The dumbbell feet elevated figure four glute bridge is an advanced unilateral variation that targets the gluteus maximus, gluteus medius, and hip flexors. The figure four position creates additional hip external rotation and challenges single-leg stability while the elevation increases the range of motion.
steps: Lie on your back with one foot elevated on a bench or platform
Cross your opposite ankle over the knee of the elevated leg (figure four position)
Place a dumbbell on the hip of your working side for added resistance
Keep your arms at your sides for stability and support the weight
Drive through the heel of your elevated foot to lift your hips up
Focus on squeezing the glute of your working leg at the top
Feel the stretch in your hip flexors and glute activation
Lower your hips slowly back toward the ground with control
Complete all reps on one side before switching to the other leg

products.title: Dumbbell Elbow Side Plank
products.description: The dumbbell elbow side plank is an advanced core exercise that targets the obliques, transverse abdominis, and quadratus lumborum. Adding a dumbbell increases the resistance and challenges lateral core stability, improving anti-lateral flexion strength and overall core endurance.
steps: Lie on your side with your elbow directly under your shoulder
Place a dumbbell on your top hip and hold it in place with your free hand
Stack your feet or place the top foot in front for more stability
Engage your core and lift your hips off the ground
Create a straight line from your head to your feet
Keep your shoulders stacked and avoid letting your hips rotate
Hold the position while maintaining steady breathing
Focus on feeling the contraction in your obliques
Complete the hold time before switching to the other side

products.title: Dumbbell Decline Close Neutral Grip Press
products.description: The dumbbell decline close neutral grip press is a chest-focused compound exercise performed on a decline bench with a narrow, neutral grip. This variation targets the lower pectoralis major, triceps, and anterior deltoids while reducing stress on the shoulders and wrists compared to traditional pressing grips. The decline angle emphasizes the lower chest development while the close grip increases tricep activation.
steps: Set up on a decline bench with dumbbells held at chest level
Hold dumbbells with neutral grip (palms facing each other) close together
Position dumbbells directly over your lower chest with arms extended
Lower the dumbbells slowly by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body
Descend until you feel a stretch in your chest muscles
Press the dumbbells back up by extending your arms, focusing on contracting your chest
Keep the dumbbells close together throughout the movement
Maintain control and avoid bouncing at the bottom position

products.title: Dumbbell Chest Supported Y Raise
products.description: The dumbbell chest supported Y raise is an isolation exercise that targets the posterior deltoids, rhomboids, and lower trapezius muscles. Performed with chest support, this movement helps improve posture, strengthens the often-neglected posterior chain, and is excellent for shoulder rehabilitation. The Y-pattern motion specifically targets the muscles responsible for scapular retraction and upward rotation.
steps: Set an incline bench to 45-60 degrees and lie chest down with dumbbells in each hand
Let your arms hang naturally with a slight bend in your elbows
Start with your arms in a neutral position hanging straight down
Raise both arms up and out to form a 'Y' shape with your body
Focus on squeezing your shoulder blades together and lifting through your rear delts
Pause at the top when your arms are roughly parallel to your torso
Lower the weights slowly back to the starting position with control
Keep your chest pressed against the bench throughout the movement

products.title: Dumbbell Alternating Pendlay Row
products.description: The dumbbell row is a fundamental pulling exercise that primarily targets the latissimus dorsi, rhomboids, middle trapezius. This compound movement also engages the rear deltoids, biceps, lower trapezius, helping to improve posture, strengthen the posterior chain, and build overall upper body pulling strength.
steps: Position yourself properly with the dumbbell, maintaining good posture
Engage your core and establish a stable base of support
Begin the movement with control, focusing on proper form
Move through the full range of motion with deliberate precision
Maintain tension in the target muscles throughout the exercise
Control both the concentric and eccentric phases of the movement
Breathe properly - exhale during exertion, inhale during the return phase
Complete the prescribed repetitions while maintaining perfect technique

products.title: Dumbbell Alternating Arnold Press
products.description: The dumbbell alternating Arnold press is a dynamic shoulder exercise named after Arnold Schwarzenegger that combines rotation with pressing movement. This exercise targets the anterior and medial deltoids while engaging the rotator cuff muscles throughout the full range of motion. The alternating pattern challenges core stability and coordination while building functional pressing strength.
steps: Sit on a bench with back support, holding dumbbells at shoulder height
Start with palms facing your body and elbows bent at 90 degrees
Begin pressing one dumbbell up while rotating your wrist outward
As you press, rotate your palm from facing you to facing forward
Continue pressing until your arm is fully extended overhead
Lower the dumbbell while reversing the rotation back to starting position
Alternate arms, performing the same rotation and press with the other side
Keep your core engaged and maintain control throughout the movement

products.title: Dragonfly
products.description: The dragonfly is an extremely advanced core exercise that primarily targets the rectus abdominis, hip flexors, and deep core stabilizers. Made famous by Bruce Lee, this challenging movement requires exceptional core strength, shoulder stability, and body control while building incredible abdominal power.
steps: Lie on your back on a bench, gripping the bench behind your head for support
Keep your shoulders firmly planted on the bench throughout the movement
Start with your body straight and legs extended, forming a line from head to toe
Engage your core and slowly lower your legs while keeping them straight
Maintain a straight body line - avoid letting your hips bend or sag
Lower until your body is nearly horizontal or as far as you can control
Use your core strength to reverse the movement back to starting position
Keep your grip tight on the bench and shoulders stable throughout
Breathe steadily and avoid using momentum
This is an elite-level exercise - master easier core progressions first

products.title: Downward Dog With Fingers Facing Feet
products.description: Downward Dog with fingers facing feet is an advanced yoga variation that intensely stretches the wrists, forearms, and shoulders while strengthening the core and legs. This challenging pose reverses the typical hand position, creating a deeper stretch through the anterior forearms and improving wrist flexibility. It requires significant wrist mobility and should be approached gradually.
steps: Start in a standard downward-facing dog position
Carefully lift one hand and rotate it 180 degrees so fingers point toward your feet
Repeat with the other hand, ensuring both palms remain flat on the ground
Keep your arms straight and shoulders active to protect your wrists
Press firmly through your palms while lengthening through your spine
Hold the position while breathing deeply and steadily
Keep your core engaged to support your lower back
To exit, carefully rotate your hands back to normal position one at a time

products.description: Crow pose (Bakasana) is an advanced arm balance that targets the wrists, forearms, core, and hip flexors. steps: Start in a deep squat with your feet close together
Place your palms flat on the ground in front of you, fingers spread wide

Shift your weight forward onto your hands and engage your core
Slowly lift your toes off the ground, one foot at a time
Keep your gaze forward and maintain a strong grip with your fingers
Engage your core to keep your knees close to your elbows
Hold the position while breathing steadily
To exit, slowly lower your toes back to the ground
Rest in child's pose to stretch your wrists after holding

products.description: The cross body shoulder stretch targets the posterior deltoids, rhomboids, and the posterior capsule of the shoulder joint. steps: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and good posture
Bring your right arm across your body at chest level
Use your left hand to gently pull your right arm closer to your chest
Keep your shoulders square and avoid rotating your torso
Feel the stretch in the back of your right shoulder
Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds while breathing deeply
Keep your arm straight or slightly bent at the elbow
Release slowly and repeat on the opposite side
Avoid forcing the stretch - gentle pressure is sufficient

Engage your core and raise the ball high above your head
Slam the ball down to the ground with maximum force
Use your entire body to generate power through the movement
Squat down to pick up the ball after it bounces
Immediately return to the starting position for the next rep
Maintain control while moving explosively
Focus on using your core and shoulders to drive the movement

products.description: The tennis forehand ground stroke is a fundamental tennis technique that involves hitting the ball after it bounces on your dominant side. This movement develops rotational power, hand-eye coordination, and sport-specific movement patterns.
steps: Start in ready position with feet shoulder-width apart
Turn your shoulders and step forward with your non-dominant foot
Take the racket back early with your dominant hand
Keep your eye on the ball throughout the movement
Rotate your hips and shoulders through the swing
Make contact with the ball at waist height
Follow through across your body with the racket finishing high
Return to ready position for the next shot

Set your desired speed and resistance level
Step up with full foot contact on each step
Keep your posture upright with core engaged
Use a natural stepping motion, lifting your knees
Avoid leaning heavily on the rails
Maintain a steady rhythm throughout the workout

Begin with gentle bouncing, keeping feet in contact with the surface
Gradually increase the intensity while maintaining control
Keep your core engaged and posture upright
Land softly on the balls of your feet
Use your arms for balance and momentum
Maintain a steady rhythm throughout the exercise
Start with short sessions and gradually increase duration

Begin with gentle bouncing to establish rhythm
Lift one knee high toward your chest while bouncing
Alternate legs, pushing each knee up with intention
Keep your core engaged throughout the movement
Use your arms for balance and momentum
Maintain control while increasing the knee height
Land softly on the rebounder surface

Begin bouncing to establish momentum
Jump up and bring both knees toward your chest simultaneously
Land softly back on the rebounder surface
Use your arms to help generate upward momentum
Keep your core tight during the knee tuck
Maintain control throughout the jumping motion
Start with lower jumps and gradually increase intensity

Begin with a gentle bounce to establish rhythm
Jump your feet apart while raising your arms overhead
Jump your feet back together while lowering your arms
Maintain the jumping jack pattern while bouncing
Keep your core engaged throughout the movement
Land softly on the rebounder surface
Coordinate your arm and leg movements smoothly

Step or jump back down to the ground
Repeat the sequence in a controlled manner
Keep your core engaged during transitions
Land softly when moving between surfaces
Focus on smooth, coordinated movements

Lift your knees high toward your chest with each step
Pump your arms in a natural running motion
Maintain a quick, light cadence
Keep your core engaged and posture upright
Focus on lifting knees rather than jumping high
Breathe rhythmically throughout the exercise

Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, core engaged
Push the handle forward with controlled force
Keep your shoulders stable and core tight
Pull the handle back to the starting position
Maintain proper posture throughout the movement
Control both the pushing and pulling phases
Coordinate the movement with proper breathing

products.description: Push pull chair overhead pull is a functional exercise that involves pulling a weighted chair or object overhead. This movement develops full-body strength, coordination, and simulates real-world lifting and pulling motions.

Grip the chair securely with both hands
Engage your core and establish a stable stance
Pull the chair up and over your head
Use your entire body to generate pulling force
Control the movement in both directions
Keep your back straight throughout the exercise
Return to the starting position with control

products.description: Multi hip glute extension uses a specialized machine to target the glutes through hip extension. This exercise isolates the gluteus maximus while providing stability and support, making it effective for glute strengthening and activation.

Adjust the machine to fit your height
Place the back of your thigh against the pad
Hold the handles for stability
Extend your hip by pushing your leg back
Squeeze your glute at the end of the movement
Return to the starting position with control
Complete all reps before switching legs

Adjust the machine to fit your height and range of motion
Place your leg against the pad on the outside
Hold the handles for stability

Squeeze your inner thigh muscles at the peak
Return to the starting position with control
Complete all reps before switching legs

Adjust the machine to fit your height properly
Place your leg against the pad on the inside
Hold the handles for stability and support
Push your leg away from your body
Focus on using your outer hip and glute muscles
Return to the starting position with control
Complete all reps before switching legs

Lift your knees 2-3 inches off the ground
Keep your back flat and core engaged

Keep your knees low but not touching the ground

Position the barbell across your shoulders in rack position
Keep your core engaged and back straight

Maintain tension in your core throughout the movement

products.title: Barbell Supinated Pendlay Row
products.description: Barbell supinated Pendlay row uses an underhand grip while performing the Pendlay row. This variation emphasizes the biceps and lower lats while building explosive pulling power from a dead stop position on each rep.

Use an underhand (supinated) grip, hands shoulder-width apart
Hinge at the hips with your torso parallel to the floor
Explosively pull the barbell to your lower chest
Squeeze your lats and biceps at the top
Lower the barbell back to the floor completely

Step up onto the box with one foot

Raise your arms out to the sides to shoulder height
Rotate your arms so your palms face up

products.description: Barbell Spoto press involves pausing the barbell 1-2 inches above the chest rather than touching. This variation builds strength in the sticking point of the bench press while improving control and muscle tension.

Lower the barbell to 1-2 inches above your chest
Pause in this position for 1-2 seconds
Do not let the barbell touch your chest

Maintain tension throughout the pause
Keep your shoulder blades retracted
Control the weight during both phases

products.description: Barbell situp adds resistance to the traditional situp by holding a barbell across the chest. This exercise targets the rectus abdominis and hip flexors while building core strength and stability under load.

Hold a barbell across your chest with both hands
Keep the barbell secure against your chest
Sit up by flexing your spine and engaging your abs
Rise until your torso is upright
Lower back down to the starting position with control
Keep your feet planted throughout the movement
Focus on using your core muscles to lift

Stand with feet shoulder-width apart
Pull your shoulders back and up in a circular motion
Emphasize the backward component of the movement
Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top
Hold the contraction briefly
Lower your shoulders back to the starting position
Avoid rolling your shoulders forward

products.title: Barbell Side Step Up
products.description: Barbell side step up involves stepping sideways onto a platform while holding a barbell. This lateral movement targets the glutes, quadriceps, and adductors while improving frontal plane stability and strength.
steps: Hold a barbell across your shoulders in back squat position
Stand perpendicular to a box or platform
Step sideways onto the platform with your near leg
Drive through your heel to stand completely on the platform
Step down to the starting position with control
Keep your torso upright throughout the movement
Complete all reps on one side before switching
Focus on the working leg doing most of the work

products.title: Barbell Reverse Deadlift
products.description: Barbell reverse deadlift involves lowering the barbell from a standing position rather than lifting it from the floor. This eccentric-focused variation builds strength in the lowering phase while teaching proper hip hinge mechanics.
steps: Start standing upright with the barbell at hip level
Keep your chest up and shoulders back
Hinge at the hips and push them back
Lower the barbell toward the floor with control
Keep the barbell close to your body throughout
Feel the stretch in your hamstrings
Reverse the movement to return to standing
Focus on controlling the eccentric (lowering) phase

products.title: Barbell Press Under
products.description: Barbell press under is a mobility drill that involves pressing the barbell overhead while squatting under it. This exercise improves overhead mobility, shoulder stability, and teaches the receiving position for Olympic lifts.
steps: Start with the barbell at shoulder height
Press the barbell overhead while simultaneously squatting down
Catch the barbell in a deep squat position with arms extended
Keep your core engaged and chest up
Stand up while maintaining the overhead position
Lower the barbell back to shoulder height
Focus on smooth coordination between pressing and squatting
Start with light weight to master the movement pattern

products.title: Barbell Meadows Row
products.description: Barbell Meadows row is a single-arm rowing variation using a barbell in a landmine setup. This exercise targets the lats, rhomboids, and rear delts while allowing for a longer range of motion and unilateral training benefits.
steps: Set up a barbell in a landmine or corner
Stand perpendicular to the barbell
Grab the end of the barbell with your far hand
Hinge at the hips and lean over slightly
Row the barbell toward your lower ribcage
Squeeze your lat and rhomboids at the top
Lower the weight with control
Complete all reps before switching sides

products.title: Barbell Long Landmine Row
products.description: Barbell long landmine row involves rowing the barbell from a longer distance in the landmine setup. This variation provides an extended range of motion and emphasizes the lats and middle traps while allowing for heavy loading.
steps: Set up a barbell in a landmine position
Stand further back from the landmine to create a longer lever
Grab the end of the barbell with both hands
Hinge at the hips and maintain a neutral spine
Row the barbell toward your lower chest
Focus on squeezing your shoulder blades together
Lower the weight back to the starting position
Maintain tension throughout the full range of motion

products.description: Barbell Larsen bench press is performed with feet elevated off the ground, eliminating leg drive and arch. This variation increases chest and tricep activation while improving core stability and teaching proper upper body pressing mechanics.
steps: Lie on the bench and lift your feet off the ground
Keep your knees bent and feet elevated throughout
Grip the barbell with your normal bench press grip
Lower the barbell to your chest with control
Press the barbell back up using only your upper body
Keep your core engaged to maintain stability
Avoid using any leg drive or excessive arch
Focus on controlled movement throughout

steps: Set up a barbell in a landmine position
Hold the end of the barbell with both hands
Stand with feet shoulder-width apart
Keep the barbell at chest level
Bend to one side while keeping the barbell stable
Feel the stretch in your opposite oblique
Return to center and bend to the other side
Keep your core engaged throughout the movement

products.title: Barbell landmine chest press
products.description: Barbell landmine chest press provides a unique pressing angle that targets the chest, shoulders, and triceps. The landmine setup allows for natural scapular movement while reducing stress on the shoulder joint.
steps: Set up a barbell in a landmine position
Hold the end of the barbell at chest level
Stand in a staggered stance for stability
Press the barbell forward and up at an angle
Follow the natural arc of the landmine
Squeeze your chest at the end of the movement
Return to the starting position with control
Keep your core engaged throughout the press

products.title: Barbell Jump Shrug
products.description: Barbell jump shrug combines explosive jumping with shoulder shrugging to develop power in the trapezius and entire kinetic chain. This plyometric exercise improves athletic performance and builds explosive upper body strength.
steps: Hold a barbell with an overhand grip at hip level
Stand with feet shoulder-width apart
Simultaneously jump up and shrug your shoulders
Explosively drive through your legs and shrug at the top
Land softly and immediately prepare for the next rep
Keep the barbell close to your body throughout
Focus on coordinating the jump and shrug movements
Start with lighter weight to master the timing

products.title: Barbell Hooklying Bench Press
products.description: Barbell hooklying bench press is performed lying on the floor with knees bent and feet flat. This variation reduces the range of motion and eliminates excessive arching while building strength in the lockout portion of the bench press.

Set up under the barbell as you would for regular bench press
Lower the barbell until your upper arms touch the floor
Pause briefly with arms on the floor
Press the barbell back up to full extension
Keep your shoulder blades retracted
Maintain tension in your chest and triceps
Focus on the lockout portion of the movement

Use a narrower grip on the barbell

Lower the barbell to your chest with elbows tucked

Maintain the close elbow position throughout
Control the movement in both directions

steps: Start with the barbell at hip level with an overhand grip
Keep your chest up and shoulders back
Hinge at the hips and lower the bar to mid-thigh
Explosively extend your hips and shrug your shoulders
Pull the barbell up and catch it at shoulder level
Drop into a front squat position to receive the bar
Stand up with the barbell in front rack position
Lower the bar back to the starting position

products.title: Barbell Feet Elevated Staggered Glute Bridge Male
products.description: The barbell feet elevated staggered glute bridge is an advanced unilateral variation that targets the gluteus maximus, gluteus medius, and deep hip stabilizers. With feet elevated on a platform and positioned in a staggered stance, this exercise challenges single-leg strength, balance, and coordination while building powerful hip extension. The staggered foot position creates an unstable base that demands greater core engagement.
steps: Lie on your back with feet elevated on a bench or platform
Position one foot slightly forward and the other slightly back (staggered stance)
Place the barbell across your hips, using padding if needed
Keep your arms at your sides for stability and support
Drive through both heels to lift your hips toward the ceiling
Focus on engaging the glute of the forward leg more intensely
Maintain balance while creating a straight line from knees to shoulders
Hold the top position briefly, feeling the asymmetrical challenge
Lower your hips with control, maintaining the staggered foot position

products.title: Barbell Feet Elevated Single Leg Glute Bridge Male
products.description: The barbell feet elevated single leg glute bridge is an extremely challenging unilateral exercise that targets the gluteus maximus, gluteus medius, hamstrings, and core stabilizers. By performing the movement with feet elevated and using only one leg, this exercise maximally challenges hip extension strength, balance, and stability. It's excellent for identifying and correcting strength imbalances while building serious glute power.
steps: Lie on your back with both feet elevated on a bench or platform
Lift one leg off the platform, keeping it bent at 90 degrees
Place the barbell across your hips, securing it with both hands
Keep the working leg firmly planted on the elevated surface
Drive through the heel of your working leg to lift your hips up
Push your hips as high as possible, creating maximum glute contraction
Keep your non-working leg steady and avoid using it for assistance
Hold the top position briefly, feeling the intense single-leg challenge
Lower with control, fighting gravity with your working leg only

products.description: The barbell feet elevated single leg glute bridge is an extremely challenging unilateral exercise that targets the gluteus maximus, gluteus medius, hamstrings, and core stabilizers. steps: Lie on your back with both feet elevated on a bench or platform
Lift one leg off the platform, keeping it bent at 90 degrees
Place the barbell across your hips, securing it with both hands
Keep the working leg firmly planted on the elevated surface

products.title: Dumbbell Single Arm Floor Press
products.description: The dumbbell single arm floor press is a unilateral chest pressing exercise that targets the pectoralis major, anterior deltoids, and triceps. Performed lying on the floor, this exercise provides a natural stopping point that prevents overextension and reduces shoulder stress compared to bench pressing. It's excellent for building single-arm pressing strength, improving stability, and correcting strength imbalances between sides.
steps: Lie on your back on the floor with knees bent and feet flat
Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your arm extended straight up above your chest
Keep your non-working arm extended out to the side for balance
Slowly lower the dumbbell by bending your elbow until your upper arm touches the floor
Pause briefly with your tricep resting on the floor
Press the dumbbell back up by extending your arm to the starting position
Keep your core engaged and avoid arching your back excessively
Complete all repetitions on one side before switching arms

products.title: Dumbbell Single Arm Floor Press From Close Elbow
products.description: The dumbbell single arm floor press from close elbow is a tricep-focused variation of the floor press that emphasizes the close-grip pressing pattern. By keeping the elbow closer to the body throughout the movement, this exercise shifts emphasis from the chest to the triceps while still engaging the anterior deltoids. The floor provides a natural stopping point, making it safer for the shoulders and ideal for building lockout strength.
steps: Lie on the floor with knees bent, holding a dumbbell in one hand
Start with the dumbbell at chest level, elbow positioned close to your side
Keep your elbow tucked in at approximately 45 degrees to your torso
Press the dumbbell straight up while maintaining the close elbow position
Focus on extending through the triceps rather than pushing out wide
Lower the weight slowly until your upper arm touches the floor
Keep your core engaged and avoid excessive back arch
Complete all reps on one side before switching to the other arm

products.title: Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Cross Raise
products.description: The dumbbell standing single arm cross raise is a unilateral shoulder isolation exercise that targets the anterior and medial deltoids. This cross-body movement pattern challenges shoulder stability and coordination while building strength through a unique range of motion. The single-arm execution allows for focused muscle engagement and helps identify and correct strength imbalances between sides.
steps: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand
Keep your torso upright with core engaged throughout the movement
Start with the dumbbell hanging at your side opposite to the working arm
Lift the dumbbell up and across your body toward the opposite shoulder
Keep a slight bend in your elbow as you raise the weight
Focus on leading the movement with your shoulder, not your hand
Pause briefly at the top, feeling tension in your deltoid
Lower the weight slowly back across your body to the starting position
Complete all repetitions on one side before switching arms

products.title: Dumbbell Standing Svend Press
products.description: The dumbbell standing Svend press is an isometric and concentric chest exercise that emphasizes the inner pectoralis major fibers. Named after strongman Svend Karlsen, this exercise involves pressing dumbbells together at chest level and then extending them away from the body. The constant squeezing motion creates intense tension in the chest muscles while also engaging the anterior deltoids and triceps.
steps: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding two dumbbells at chest height
Press the flat sides of the dumbbells together at the center of your chest
Keep your elbows slightly bent and parallel to the ground
Squeeze the dumbbells firmly together throughout the entire movement
Slowly press the dumbbells straight out away from your chest
Maintain the squeezing pressure between the weights at all times
Hold for a brief pause when your arms are fully extended
Slowly bring the dumbbells back to your chest while maintaining the squeeze
Keep your core engaged and avoid leaning forward or backward

products.title: Dumbbell Tate Press
products.description: The dumbbell Tate press is an advanced tricep isolation exercise that targets the triceps with an emphasis on the medial and lateral heads. Named after powerlifter Dave Tate, this exercise uses a unique elbow-out movement pattern where the dumbbells are lowered to the chest in an arc motion. This exercise is excellent for building tricep strength and mass, particularly for improving bench press lockout strength.
steps: Lie on a bench with feet flat on the floor, holding dumbbells directly above your chest
Start with arms fully extended and dumbbells touching each other
Keep your elbows flared out to the sides throughout the movement
Lower the dumbbells in an arc motion toward your upper chest/lower neck area
The dumbbells should move in a semi-circular path, not straight down
Focus on keeping your elbows stationary and only moving your forearms
Feel a stretch in your triceps at the bottom position
Press the dumbbells back up following the same arc path to the starting position
Maintain tension in your triceps throughout the entire range of motion

products.title: Elevated Push Up
products.description: The elevated push-up is a bodyweight exercise variation where the feet are placed on a raised surface, increasing the difficulty and shifting emphasis to the upper chest and anterior deltoids. This incline angle creates a decline push-up position that targets the clavicular portion of the pectoralis major more effectively than standard push-ups, while also engaging the core for stability.
steps: Place your feet on an elevated surface like a bench, chair, or step
Position your hands on the floor slightly wider than shoulder-width apart
Create a straight line from your head to your heels
Keep your core tight and glutes engaged throughout the movement
Lower your chest toward the floor by bending your elbows
Descend until your chest nearly touches the ground
Push through your palms to return to the starting position
Keep your elbows at approximately 45 degrees to your torso
Maintain the straight body line throughout the entire movement

products.title: Barbell Feet Elevated Glute Bridge Male
products.description: The barbell glute bridge is a hip-dominant exercise that primarily targets the gluteus maximus, gluteus medius while engaging the gluteus minimus, piriformis. This exercise builds powerful hip extension, improves glute activation, and helps counteract the effects of prolonged sitting.
steps: Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the floor
Place the barbell across your hips if using weight
Keep your arms at your sides for stability
Drive through your heels to lift your hips off the ground
Squeeze your glutes and create a straight line from knees to shoulders
Keep your core engaged and avoid pushing through your toes
Hold the top position briefly for maximum muscle activation
Lower your hips back to the ground with control

products.description: The barbell glute bridge is a hip-dominant exercise that primarily targets the gluteus maximus, gluteus medius while engaging the gluteus minimus, piriformis. products.title: Barbell Feet Elevated Figure Four Glute Bridge
products.description: The barbell feet elevated figure four glute bridge is a specialized unilateral variation that targets the gluteus maximus, gluteus medius, and deep external rotators. The figure-four leg position (ankle crossed over knee) emphasizes hip external rotation while challenging stability and glute activation. This exercise is particularly effective for strengthening the gluteus medius and addressing hip stability issues.
steps: Lie on your back with feet elevated on a bench or platform
Cross your right ankle over your left knee, creating a figure-four position
Keep your left foot firmly planted on the elevated surface
Place the barbell across your hips, holding it securely with both hands
Drive through your left heel to lift your hips up toward the ceiling
Focus on engaging the glute of the planted leg while maintaining the figure-four position
Feel the additional stretch and activation in your hip external rotators
Hold the top position briefly, emphasizing the unilateral challenge
Lower with control, then switch legs to work the other side

products.title: Barbell Deadlift High Pull
products.description: The barbell deadlift is a fundamental hip-hinge movement that primarily targets the latissimus dorsi, rhomboids, middle trapezius. This compound exercise builds posterior chain strength, improves hip mobility, and develops functional movement patterns essential for daily activities and athletic performance.
steps: Stand with feet hip-width apart, barbell positioned close to your body
Hinge at your hips by pushing them back and slightly bending your knees
Grasp the barbell with both hands using an overhand grip
Keep your chest up, shoulders back, and maintain a neutral spine
Engage your lats by pulling your shoulders down and back
Drive through your heels and extend your hips to lift the weight
Keep the weight close to your body throughout the entire movement
Return the weight to the starting position by reversing the movement

products.title: Barbell Coan Deadlift
products.description: The barbell deadlift is a fundamental hip-hinge movement that primarily targets the latissimus dorsi, rhomboids, middle trapezius. steps: Stand with feet hip-width apart, barbell positioned close to your body

Drive through your heels and extend your hips to lift the weight
Keep the weight close to your body throughout the entire movement
Return the weight to the starting position by reversing the movement

products.title: Barbell Calf Jump
products.description: The barbell calf jump is an explosive plyometric exercise that targets the gastrocnemius and soleus muscles while developing lower leg power and reactive strength. This advanced movement combines weighted calf raises with jumping mechanics, making it excellent for athletes looking to improve vertical leap, sprint acceleration, and overall lower leg explosive power.
steps: Position a barbell across your upper traps as you would for a back squat
Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing straight ahead
Keep your core tight and maintain an upright torso throughout
Rise up onto the balls of your feet, lifting your heels as high as possible
Explosively jump straight up while staying on the balls of your feet
Land softly on the balls of your feet, maintaining control
Allow your heels to briefly touch the ground before the next rep
Focus on quick, explosive calf contractions with controlled landings
Keep the barbell stable on your back throughout the jumping motion

products.title: Banded Feet Elevated Hip Thrusters
products.description: The bodyweight hip thrust is a hip-dominant exercise that primarily targets the gluteus maximus, gluteus medius while engaging the gluteus minimus, piriformis. This exercise builds powerful hip extension, improves glute activation, and helps counteract the effects of prolonged sitting.
steps: Sit with your upper back against a bench, knees bent, feet flat on the floor
Position the bodyweight across your hips if using weight
Keep your feet approximately shoulder-width apart
Drive through your heels to lift your hips up toward the ceiling
Squeeze your glutes at the top, creating a straight line from knees to shoulders
Keep your core engaged and avoid overarching your lower back
Hold the top position briefly for maximum glute contraction
Lower your hips back down with control, maintaining tension

products.title: Band Squat Row
products.description: The bodyweight row is a fundamental pulling exercise that primarily targets the latissimus dorsi, rhomboids, middle trapezius, quadriceps. This compound movement also engages the rear deltoids, biceps, lower trapezius, helping to improve posture, strengthen the posterior chain, and build overall upper body pulling strength.
steps: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, bodyweight positioned appropriately
Keep your chest up, shoulders back, and eyes looking straight ahead
Engage your core and maintain a neutral spine throughout
Initiate the movement by pushing your hips back and bending at the knees
Descend until your hip crease is just below your knee caps
Keep your weight evenly distributed across your feet
Drive through your heels and push the ground away to stand up
Maintain knee alignment over your toes throughout the movement

products.title: Band Spanish Split Squat
products.description: The bodyweight squat is a compound lower body exercise that primarily works the quadriceps, hamstrings, gluteus maximus while engaging the calves, hip flexors. This movement builds functional strength, improves hip and ankle mobility, and develops power in the lower body.
steps: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, bodyweight positioned appropriately
Keep your chest up, shoulders back, and eyes looking straight ahead
Engage your core and maintain a neutral spine throughout
Initiate the movement by pushing your hips back and bending at the knees
Descend until your hip crease is just below your knee caps
Keep your weight evenly distributed across your feet
Drive through your heels and push the ground away to stand up
Maintain knee alignment over your toes throughout the movement
